From clang&#x27;s source code:<p><pre><code>    // switch(bool_expr) {...} is often a programmer error, e.g.
    // switch(n && mask) { ... } // Doh - should be &quot;n & mask&quot;.
    // One can always use an if statement instead of switch(bool_expr).
</code></pre>
I agree that clang should not warn on this without asking for warnings and even then it should be possible to disable it. Maybe it would be a good idea to file a bug report.<p>That being said, I can&#x27;t imagine why you would ever choose to switch on a bool, and even go to the trouble to add a cast instead of just writing an if statement.<p>Also, my clang and g++ with &quot;-Wall -Wextra&quot; does not warn on an empty while statement.
